<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1325,1044,1870]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,439,1164,1190]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Vesica largely developed, sternite 
<number box="[854,883,1164,1190]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="10.0">10</number>
divided into pair of digitiform distal sclerites, parameres well sclerotized, distally bifid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1325,1044,1870]" box="[312,457,1244,1270]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,457,1244,1270]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1325,1044,1870]" box="[312,922,1284,1310]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[435,538,1284,1309]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Anapausis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wirthi">
<emphasis box="[435,538,1284,1309]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">A. wirthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in all aspects, except as follows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1325,1044,1870]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis box="[312,380,1324,1349]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Male.</emphasis>
Measurements (in mm). Body length, 1.74; wing length, 1.20; wing width, 0.50. Color. Dark brown specimens, mouthparts ochre­yellowish, antennae ochre. Thoracic sclerites ochre, scutum slightly darker; legs brownish ochre, except light ochre tarsi. Wings translucent, except brownish veins, posterior ones lighter. Tergites brown, sternites light brown. Terminalia brown. Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[826,931,1484,1510]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="11.[264,368,1065,1089]" captionTargetBox="[275,1312,326,1041]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[275,1312,326,1041]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 12. Anapausis mayana. Thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173632/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[898,931,1484,1510]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Antepronotal setae, 
<number box="[1239,1316,1484,1510]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="28.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="26.0">26–30</number>
; proepisternals, 
<number box="[455,472,1524,1550]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="6.0">6</number>
; proepimerals, 
<number box="[676,693,1524,1550]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="6.0">6</number>
; spiracular sclerite setae, 
<number box="[1041,1058,1524,1550]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="8.0">8</number>
; anepisternals, 
<number box="[1263,1294,1524,1550]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="14.0">14</number>
/ 
<number box="[1304,1318,1524,1550]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="8.0">8</number>
; katepisternals, 
<number box="[445,477,1564,1590]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="16.0">16</number>
; mesepimerals, 
<number box="[677,721,1564,1590]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7</number>
/ 
<number box="[732,776,1564,1590]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7</number>
; merals, 0; subspiraculars, 
<number box="[1116,1133,1564,1590]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="5.0">5</number>
; supra­alars, 
<number box="[1300,1317,1564,1590]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="4.0">4</number>
; pedicelars, absent; a number of longer scutellar setae not in regular row. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[1220,1308,1604,1630]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="11.[264,368,1687,1711]" captionTargetBox="[291,1302,1163,1676]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[270,1317,1142,1676]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 13. Anapausis mayana. Wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173633/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[1276,1308,1604,1630]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[396,540,1644,1670]" captionStart="FIGURES 14, 15" captionStartId="12.[264,382,769,793]" captionTargetBox="[269,1315,337,735]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[258,1329,326,744]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 14, 15. Anapausis mayana. Abdominal sclerites. 14. Tergite 2. 15. Sternite 4." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173634/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[463,540,1644,1670]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[705,793,1644,1670]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="12.[264,368,1802,1826]" captionText="FIGURE 16. Anapausis mayana. Male terminalia, ventral view." pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[760,793,1644,1670]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
): seminal vesica very large, aedeagus ending on short apical tube; parameres clearly present, bare, well sclerotized, distally bifid; gonostyles deeply bifid, both extensions digitiform and setose; very modified gonocoxites as pair of projections mesal to gonostyles, each with 
<number box="[901,916,1764,1790]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="3.0">3</number>
setae; T 
<number box="[1020,1033,1764,1790]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="8.0">8</number>
+ 
<number box="[1050,1064,1764,1790]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="9.0">9</number>
well developed, with pair of spiracles; S 
<number box="[489,519,1804,1830]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="10.0">10</number>
as pair of distal, finger­like projections completely separated from each other. Lobes of sternite 
<number box="[602,617,1844,1870]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="7.0">7</number>
apparently absent.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[264,851,1065,1089]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173632/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" targetBox="[275,1312,326,1041]" targetPageId="11">
