<paragraph blockId="11.[264,1321,1756,1902]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis box="[312,407,1757,1782]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Female.</emphasis>
As for male, except as follows. Terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[994,1143,1756,1782]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 19" captionStartId="13.[264,383,1189,1213]" captionTargetBox="[296,1291,340,1155]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[281,1307,326,1165]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 19. Anapausis mayana. Female terminalia. 17. Ventral view. 18. Dorsal view. 19. Lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173635/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Figs. 
<number box="[1069,1143,1756,1782]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="18.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="17.0">17–19</number>
</figureCitation>
) with pair of gonapophyses VIII. Pair of translucent lobes internally on terminalia arising anteriorly from sternite 
<number box="[431,449,1836,1862]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="9.0">9</number>
. Tergite 
<number box="[560,589,1836,1862]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="10.0">10</number>
rather well sclerotized. T 
<number box="[910,923,1836,1862]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="8.0">8</number>
+ 
<number box="[940,954,1836,1862]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="9.0">9</number>
with pair of spiracles clearly produced, vaginal furca laterally compressed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
